        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In the Programmer's Reference Guide (Section 7.5.1.), about the lighttpd rewrite rule there is:\n\n{code}\nurl.rewrite-once = (\n  \".*\\.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css)$\" => \"$0\",\n  \"\" => \"\/index.php\"\n)\n{code}\n\nBut with this rewrite rule you miss the HTTP GET parameters\n\nI suggest this rule (tested with succes on my website):\n\n{code}\nurl.rewrite-once = (\n  \".*\\.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css)$\" => \"$0\",\n  \".*\\?(.*)$\" => \"\/index.php?$1\",\n  \"\" => \"\/index.php\"\n)\n{code}\n\nRegards\n\nJean-Yves"
        },
