            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20024",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It looks like both rulesets would be susceptible to breaking when GET parameters end in the same suffixes as listed in the first rule of each ruleset. For example, URLs such as:\n\n{noformat}\nhttp:\/\/example.com\/?style=my.css\nhttp:\/\/example.com\/index\/?a=1&which=nice.gif\n{noformat}\n\nwould match the first rule and fail. Perhaps these are edge cases, however.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-20T15:32:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-20T15:32:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20029",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djiwhy",
                        "name": "djiwhy",
                        "displayName": "Jean-Yves Pell\u00e9",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You are absolutely right Darby\n\nI may have a solution, you just have to swap two lines:\n\n{code}\nurl.rewrite-once = (\n  \".*\\?(.*)$\" => \"\/index.php?$1\",\n  \".*\\.(js|ico|gif|jpg|png|css)$\" => \"$0\",\n  \"\" => \"\/index.php\"\n)\n{code}\n\n",
